OL,3,GNorth East
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA slow-moving band of rain will
OL,6,Fgradually move eastwards across all
OL,7,Fparts on Monday morning, fragmenting
OL,8,Fas it does so, with perhaps a few
OL,9,Fbrighter spells late afternoon. Breezy.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FCloudy overnight and dry,
OL,12,Fwith some occasional breaks in the
OL,13,Fcloud, allowing the temperatures to
OL,14,Ffall with widespread frost. Winds
OL,15,Fbecoming light and variable.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FAfter a frosty start, Tuesday
OL,18,Fwill be dry with some sunny spells and
OL,19,Flight winds. Cloud will slowly thicken
OL,20,Facross the south of the region by the
OL,21,Fevening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
